OL,3,C'If I can stop one parent buying an e-
OL,4,Cscooter this Christmas it's all worth
OL,5,Cit'
OL,7,FA mother who lost her son in an e-
OL,8,Fscooter accident is urging parents not
OL,9,Fto buy their children e-scooters for
OL,10,FChristmas.
OL,12,FCarly Calland's 14-year-old son Jacob
OL,13,Fdied after the e-scooter he was riding
OL,14,Fon the back of crashed into a car in
OL,15,FWythenshawe.
OL,17,FJacob suffered a serious head injury.
OL,18,FHe spent 8 days in intensive care and
OL,19,Fdied in hospital on 27 March 2025.
