OL,3,C'If I can stop one parent buying an e-
OL,4,Cscooter this Christmas it's all worth
OL,5,Cit'
OL,7,FNow Carly is hoping no other parents
OL,8,Fwill have to feel like she does.
OL,10,F"I'm giving it raw, this is my life,
OL,11,Fand I don't want you to go through
OL,12,Fwhat I'm going through. So if I can
OL,13,Fstop one parent buying their child an
OL,14,Fe-scooter this Christmas then it's all
OL,15,Fworth it," she said.
OL,17,FIn the UK it is illegal to ride e-
OL,18,Fscooters on public roads, pavements,
OL,19,For cycle lanes. But Carly says lots of
OL,20,Fparents don't know that.
