OL,7,FCarly is struggling to comprehend her
OL,8,Ffirst Christmas without Jacob, "The
OL,9,Fthought of Jacob not being here, not
OL,10,Fcoming down with his brother on
OL,11,FChristmas morning, him not being sat
OL,12,Fat the dinner table.
OL,14,F"It breaks my heart, I'm not ready for
OL,15,FChristmas."
OL,17,FShe is motivated by not wanting any
OL,18,Fother parents to feel like she does.
OL,19,F"I've lost my child, I don't want
OL,20,Fanyone else to lose their lives."
